column2: In the graph \(G = (V, E)\) where $$V = \{a, b, c, d, e, f, g, h, i\}$$ and $$E = \{(d, i), (c, g), (b, f), (f, i), (c, i), (d, e), (e, h), (a, g), (a, h), (d, g), (b, h), (c, d), (a, b) \},$$ sort the following vertices in the descending order of their degree.
The degree of a vertex is the number of neighbors it has.
Drawing the graph can be helpful, but technically one could just go down the edge list and count.
